22class PropertyCell
23 : public TorqueGeneratedPropertyCell<PropertyCell, HeapObject> {
24 public:
25 // [name]: the name of the global property.
26 DECL_GETTER(name, Tagged<Name>)
27
28 // [property_details]: details of the global property.
29 DECL_GETTER(property_details_raw, Tagged<Smi>)
30 DECL_ACQUIRE_GETTER(property_details_raw, Tagged<Smi>)
31 inline PropertyDetails property_details() const;
32 inline PropertyDetails property_details(AcquireLoadTag tag) const;
33 inline void UpdatePropertyDetailsExceptCellType(PropertyDetails details);
34
35 // [value]: value of the global property.
36 DECL_GETTER(value, Tagged<Object>)
37 DECL_ACQUIRE_GETTER(value, Tagged<Object>)
38
39 // [dependent_code]: code that depends on the type of the global property.
40 DECL_ACCESSORS(dependent_code, Tagged<DependentCode>)
41
42 // Changes the value and/or property details.
43 // For global properties:
44 inline void Transition(PropertyDetails new_details, Handle<Object> new_value);
45 // For protectors:
46 void InvalidateProtector();
47
48 static PropertyCellType InitialType(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<Object> value);
49
50 // Computes the new type of the cell's contents for the given value, but
51 // without actually modifying the details.
52 static PropertyCellType UpdatedType(Isolate* isolate,
53 Tagged<PropertyCell> cell,
54 Tagged<Object> value,
55 PropertyDetails details);
56
57 // Prepares property cell at given entry for receiving given value and sets
58 // that value. As a result the old cell could be invalidated and/or dependent
59 // code could be deoptimized. Returns the (possibly new) property cell.
60 static Handle<PropertyCell> PrepareForAndSetValue(
61 Isolate* isolate, Handle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary,
62 InternalIndex entry, Handle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details);
63
64 void ClearAndInvalidate(ReadOnlyRoots roots);
65 static Handle<PropertyCell> InvalidateAndReplaceEntry(
66 Isolate* isolate, Handle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary,
67 InternalIndex entry, PropertyDetails new_details,
68 Handle<Object> new_value);
69
70 // Whether or not the {details} and {value} fit together. This is an
71 // approximation with false positives.
72 static bool CheckDataIsCompatible(PropertyDetails details,
73 Tagged<Object> value);
74
75 DECL_PRINTER(PropertyCell)
76 DECL_VERIFIER(PropertyCell)
77
78 using BodyDescriptor = FixedBodyDescriptor<kNameOffset, kSize, kSize>;
79
80 TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(PropertyCell)
81
82 private:
83 friend class Factory;
84
85 DECL_SETTER(name, Tagged<Name>)
86 DECL_SETTER(value, Tagged<Object>)
87 DECL_RELEASE_SETTER(value, Tagged<Object>)
88 DECL_SETTER(property_details_raw, Tagged<Smi>)
89 DECL_RELEASE_SETTER(property_details_raw, Tagged<Smi>)
90
91#ifdef DEBUG
92 // Whether the property cell can transition to the given state. This is an
93 // approximation with false positives.
94 bool CanTransitionTo(PropertyDetails new_details,
95 Tagged<Object> new_value) const;
96#endif // DEBUG
97};

105

107
108 // [dependent_code]: code that depends on the constness of the value.
109 DECL_ACCESSORS(dependent_code, Tagged<DependentCode>)
110
111 DECL_PRINTER(ConstTrackingLetCell)

113

116
117 TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(ConstTrackingLetCell)
118
119 private:

121};
